    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nOccasionally, when using the Svelte language server with `textDocument/linkedEditingRange`, I get the following error:\n\n```\nvim.schedule callback: .../share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/linked_editing_range.lua:157: Invalid 'end_row': out of range\nstack traceback:\n\t[C]: in function 'nvim_buf_set_extmark'\n\t.../share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/linked_editing_range.lua:157: in function 'handler'\n\t.../share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/linked_editing_range.lua:187: in function 'handler'\n\t/usr/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/client.lua:743: in function ''\n\tvim/_editor.lua: in function <vim/_editor.lua:0>\n```\n\n### Steps to reproduce using \"nvim --clean -u minimal_init.lua\"\n\nConfig:\n\n```lua\nvim.lsp.config(\"svelte\", {\n\tcmd = { \"svelteserver\", \"--stdio\" },\n\tfiletypes = { \"svelte\" },\n\t-- NOTE: setting `root_markers` directly does NOT trigger the issue\n\troot_dir = function(bufnr, on_dir)\n\t\tlocal root_files = { \"Bar.svelte\" }\n\t\tlocal fname = vim.api.nvim_buf_get_name(bufnr)\n\t\ton_dir(vim.fs.dirname(vim.fs.find(root_files, { path = fname, upward = true })[1]))\n\tend,\n})\n\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd(\"LspAttach\", {\n\tcallback = function()\n\t\tvim.lsp.linked_editing_range.enable(true, nil)\n\tend,\n})\n\nvim.lsp.enable(\"svelte\")\n```\n\nBar.svelte:\n\n```svelte\n<script lang=\"ts\">\n    import Foo from \"./Foo.svelte\";\n</script>\n\n<Foo />\n```\n\nFoo.svelte:\n\n```svelte\n<script lang=\"ts\">\n    let {\n        foo,\n    }: {\n        foo?: number;\n    } = $props();\n</script>\n```\n\nSteps:\n\n1. `nvim -u repro.lua Bar.svelte`\n2. `Ge<C-]`\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNo error\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev-1666+ge9b6474ae7\n\n### Language server name/version\n\nsvelte-language-server 0.17.22\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux 6.17.8\n\n### Log file\n\n_No response_",
