            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "This kind of stuff is common because of all the asynchronous logic happeing. We need to start building up some util functions that do something reasonable if buffer contents change or whatever. \n\nIt's tricky to solve generally without also losing the ability to find actual bugs, but an easy, generalized approach would be to \"retry once\" (or twice... ðŸ˜‚ ). \n\nExample:\n\n- https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/36592\n\nLater, a more targeted approach could be to have a few functions that encapsulate desired behaviors, e.g. \"log and continue if the error was out-of-bounds, ...\"",
